                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" corresp="http://syriaca.org/persons http://syriaca.org/authors">
                        <quote source="#bib785-1">Holy man and bp. His Syr. name is written with
                            final <foreign rend="italic" xml:lang="en-x-gedsh">ālaph</foreign>,
                            which has led modern scholars to read ‘Theodota’ or ‘Theodote’.</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" resp="http://syriaca.org" corresp="http://syriaca.org/q http://syriaca.org/saints">In hagiography: Theodute was the Bishop
                        of Amida. He was born in Ingilene and was a monk at Qenneshrin. He served
                        the poor. He taught chant to the monks at Qartmin. He was known to travel
                        with a bag full of relics to use in healing others.</note>
